data.title: PACERS MAKE 8-PLAYER TRADE WITH WARRIORS
data.meta_description: Indianapolis, Jan. 17, 2007 -- The Indiana Pacers announced Wednesday an eight-player deal with the Golden State Warriors. The Pacers received from the Warriors forwards Mike Dunleavy, Troy Murphy, Ike Diogu and guard Keith McLeod in exchange for forwards Al Harrington and Josh Powell and guards Stephen Jackson and Sarunas Jasikevicius.
